QUESTION 3:

A)System calls required to copy one file to another
open() – Opens the source and destination files
read() – Reads data from the source file
write() – Writes data to the destination file
close() – Closes both files after the operaition

B) purpose of two system call in content copying
1. read()
Reads data from the source file into a buffer
Returns the number of bytes read If it returns 0, it indicates the end of the file (EOF)
2. write()
Writes the data stored in the buffer to the destination file
Returns the number of bytes successfully written

C) pseudo code for copying the content from one to another file
START
Opensource file in READ mode
Create/Open destination file in WRITE mode

WHILE data is available in source file
    Read data into buffer
    Write buffer to destination file

END WHILE
Close source file
Close destination file
STOP

QUESTION 4:

A) Purpose of fork() and exec() system calls
fork():
Creates a new child process by duplicating the parent process
exec():
Replaces the current process image with a new program
It is usually called by the child process after fork() to execute another program

B) Role of wait() system call:
wait() makes the parent process wait until the child process finishes execution.
It prevents the creation of zombie processes.it also allow the parent to obtain the childs properties(exit...)

C) 
Start
pid = fork()
if (pid == 0){
    exec("new_program")
}else{
    wait()
    print("Child process completed")}
Stop
END

